                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.581,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 140873,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has our opinion this morning in Case 10-1472, Taniguchi versus Kan Pacific Saipan."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.581,
                        "stop": 181.394,
                        "byte_start": 140873,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15068,
                            "name": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/samuel_alito_jr",
                            "last_name": "Alito",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2712,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1138687200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2712"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32684,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44799,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/samuel_a_alito_jr_1.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 3531,
                            "identifier": "samuel_alito_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.581,
                                "stop": 12.647,
                                "byte_start": 140873,
                                "byte_stop": 157174,
                                "text": "This case concerns the terms \u0022interpreter\u0022 and \u0022translator\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.647,
                                "stop": 23.04,
                                "byte_start": 157174,
                                "byte_stop": 198760,
                                "text": "A federal statute, 28 U.S.C. Section 1920 entitles the prevailing party in a civil case to recover certain costs from the loosing party."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.04,
                                "stop": 29.519,
                                "byte_start": 198760,
                                "byte_stop": 224674,
                                "text": "The Court Interpreters Act amended this provision to include \u0022compensation of interpreters\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.519,
                                "stop": 40.6,
                                "byte_start": 224674,
                                "byte_stop": 268978,
                                "text": "The question here is whether compensation of interpreters covers the costs of producing English language versions of documents that are written in another language."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.6,
                                "stop": 52.954,
                                "byte_start": 268978,
                                "byte_stop": 318401,
                                "text": "This is a personal injury suit brought by a professional Japanese basketball player, Kouichi Taniguchi against the owner of a property on which the plaintiff was injured, Kan Pacific Saipan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.954,
                                "stop": 58.239,
                                "byte_start": 318401,
                                "byte_stop": 339508,
                                "text": "The plaintiff lost the case and the District Court awarded costs to the defendant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.239,
                                "stop": 67.348,
                                "byte_start": 339508,
                                "byte_stop": 375975,
                                "text": "These costs included the expense of translating from Japanese to English certain documents that the defendant used in preparing its defense."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.348,
                                "stop": 69.785,
                                "byte_start": 375975,
                                "byte_stop": 385693,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit affirmed the award."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.785,
                                "stop": 80.743,
                                "byte_start": 385693,
                                "byte_stop": 429474,
                                "text": "It concluded that compensation of interpreters is not limited to the cost of translating live speech but reasonably encompasses the cost of translating written documents."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.743,
                                "stop": 81.734,
                                "byte_start": 429474,
                                "byte_stop": 433445,
                                "text": "We disagree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.734,
                                "stop": 96.778,
                                "byte_start": 433445,
                                "byte_stop": 493631,
                                "text": "Because the term \u0022interpreter\u0022 is not defined in the statute, we give the word its ordinary meaning and it is not customary to speak of the interpretation of a written document from one language into another."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.778,
                                "stop": 100.755,
                                "byte_start": 493631,
                                "byte_stop": 509618,
                                "text": "Instead, the term that is customarily used is \u0022translation\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.755,
                                "stop": 116.188,
                                "byte_start": 509618,
                                "byte_stop": 571267,
                                "text": "At the time of the statute\u0027s enactments -- enactment, dictionaries uniformly define \u0022interpreter\u0022 to include persons who translate orally but only a handful define the word broadly enough to encompass translators of written materials."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.188,
                                "stop": 124.471,
                                "byte_start": 571267,
                                "byte_stop": 604390,
                                "text": "One of the few dictionaries in the latter category was the Oxford English Dictionary, but the OED\u0027s treatment is illustrative."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.471,
                                "stop": 133.12,
                                "byte_start": 604390,
                                "byte_stop": 639080,
                                "text": "The OED stated that the use of the term \u0022interpret\u0022 to refer to the translation of written documents had become obsolete."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.12,
                                "stop": 142.122,
                                "byte_start": 639080,
                                "byte_stop": 675025,
                                "text": "Any definition of the word that is absent from many dictionaries and is deemed obsolete in others is hardly a common or ordinary meaning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.122,
                                "stop": 149.327,
                                "byte_start": 675025,
                                "byte_stop": 703864,
                                "text": "We, therefore, conclude that the term \u0022interpreter\u0022 is normally understood as one who translates orally from one language to another."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 149.327,
                                "stop": 159.689,
                                "byte_start": 703864,
                                "byte_stop": 745347,
                                "text": "Nothing in the Court Interpreters Act or in other provisions of Section 1920 hints that Congress intended to go beyond this ordinary meaning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.689,
                                "stop": 163.594,
                                "byte_start": 745347,
                                "byte_stop": 760916,
                                "text": "All of this is explained in greater detail in our opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.594,
                                "stop": 174.32,
                                "byte_start": 760916,
                                "byte_stop": 803861,
                                "text": "For anyone who is interested, the opinion is written in English. Anybody [Laughter] who wants to read it in another language will have to pay to have it translated [Laughter] not interpreted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.32,
                                "stop": 181.394,
                                "byte_start": 803861,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has filed a dissenting opinion, in which Justice Breyer and Justice Sotomayor have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
